Easy Bean Salad with Salsa Verde
  --Isabelle Easter

1 medium jalapeño pepper, seeded and minced
1 large clove garlic, minced
1/4 c minced fresh cilantro leaves and tender stems
1/4 c minced fresh flat-leaf parsley leaves and tender stems
2 tbsp minced sweet onion
2 tbsp lime juice
1 1/2 tbsp evoo
3/4 tsp salt, divided
1/2 c frozen fire-roasted corn
15 oz can no-salt-added cannellini beans, rinsed
15 can no-salt-added pinto beans, rinsed
2 medium radishes, quartered and thinly sliced

Arrange minced jalapeño, garlic, cilantro, parsley and onion on a cutting board. Chop together until very finely minced. Transfer to a large bowl and stir in lime juice, oil and 1/4 tsp salt. Microwave corn in a small bowl on High until thawed, ~45 s. Add the corn, rinsed cannellini beans and pinto beans, sliced radishes and the remaining 1/2 tsp salt to the herb mixture. Toss until evenly coated. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hr before serving. 


Notes: can sub poblano for less spicy

